OL,1,D]S737{kkkc5FPolice officer sacked for  
OL,2,D]S555{jjj25Fstamping on man's head     
OL,3,D]Suuu{rrzq5F                           
OL,4,T#######################################
OL,5, A police officer who stamped on a man's
OL,6, head while he was arresting him has    
OL,7, been sacked, a watchdog has said.      
OL,9,FPC Cameron Lindley, of West Yorkshire  
OL,10,FPolice, was called to a disturbance in 
OL,11,FBradford on 1 December 2021 when       
OL,12,Fcolleagues asked for urgent support.   
OL,14,FThe Independent Office for Police      
OL,15,FConduct (IOPC) said PC Lindley "applied
OL,16,Fforce to the man's head with the sole  
OL,17,Fof his boot" when he was on the ground.
OL,19,FHis actions were found to amount to    
OL,20,Fgross misconduct.                      
